<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,392,518,544]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by the following combination of characters: body globose; head and pronotum uniformly and strongly punctate; frons swollen; frontoclypeal region with a small, smooth swelling medial to each eye; eye dorsally at posterior end of gena narrow, eight to ten facets wide, interocular distance separated by approximately 
<number box="[442,500,679,705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
times maximal eye width; basal pronotal border not margined; elytra with eight striae, surface lightly shagreened, microsculpture coarser towards apex; hind wing brachypterous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,618,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[496,612,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Male. Length: 
<quantity box="[799,893,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, humeral width: 
<quantity box="[1091,1185,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Body form globose (
<figureCitation box="[374,447,839,865]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[383,1211,316,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[352,1244,312,1418]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal view of male Canthidium margaritae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173659/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[433,447,839,865]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head and pronotum coppery­red, elytra dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1185,839,865]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1428,1452]" captionTargetBox="[383,1211,316,1407]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[352,1244,312,1418]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal view of male Canthidium margaritae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173659/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1185,839,865]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head and pronotum strongly punctate and devoid of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Clypeus rugosely punctate, apex strongly bidentate, median emargination broadly Vshaped (
<figureCitation box="[364,438,959,985]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[422,438,959,985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a); eye dorsally at posterior end of gena narrow, eight to ten facets wide, eyes separated by approximately 
<number box="[672,731,999,1025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
times maximum eye width (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1163,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1147,1163,999,1025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Frons and vertex of head strongly punctate, frons swollen; two small, black, smooth swellings between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[437,508,1079,1105]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[492,508,1079,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Pronotum on disc and posterior angles slightly shagreened; surface strongly and uniformly punctate; lateral fovea oval; posterior margin lacking elongated punctures or groove.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Elytral striae consisting of clear indented lines interrupted by fairly evenly spaced oval punctures (approximately the maximum length of one puncture); intervals shiny, finely punctate; surface shiny and slightly shagreened especially towards apex. Elytra globose; hindwing brachypterous (
<figureCitation box="[564,635,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[619,635,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
h).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Pygidium distinctly punctate, more coarsely so in basal half, surface shiny and slightly shagreened at base. Genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[675,745,1439,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[729,745,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="g" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Protibia with three teeth on external border (
<figureCitation box="[846,933,1479,1505]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[903,919,1479,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
c
</figureCitation>
), inner apical margin of protibia produced into a rounded anterior projection and slightly bent downwards (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1230,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1200,1216,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
c
</figureCitation>
), apical spur with incurved apex (
<figureCitation box="[563,649,1559,1585]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[619,636,1559,1585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
c
</figureCitation>
). Pro­, meso­ and metafemora with ventral surface finely punctate and finely shagreened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,424,1638,1664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Allotype.</emphasis>
Female. Length: 
<quantity box="[639,734,1639,1665]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
, humeral width: 
<quantity box="[938,1035,1639,1665]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Differing from male in the following major characters: clypeus slightly more transversely rugose (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1215,1679,1705]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1199,1215,1679,1705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b), apical spur not forming incurved apex and claw­bearing protarsus not as thick (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1292,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1292,1719,1745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d), pygidium broader and less heavily punctate (
<figureCitation box="[817,891,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[876,891,1759,1785]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
f), last abdominal segment broader, inner apex of protibia not forming a rounded lobe (
<figureCitation box="[861,932,1799,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. C" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1659,1683]" captionTargetBox="[304,1271,444,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1288,416,1658]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. C. margaritae. a) Dorsal view of male head; b) dorsal view of female head; c) dorsal view of right male protibia; d) dorsal view of right female protibia; e) male pygidium; f) female pygidium; g) lateral view of aedeagus; h) dorsal view of brachypterous right wing of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,932,1799,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,518,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1838,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Variation.</emphasis>
Elytral surface can range from completely shagreened to shagreened only on the apical third.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
